<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3145] JSON protocol does not handle bool and empty containers correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3145</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using Thrift to communicate with Apache Aurora and have had to make a couple of changes to the JSON protocol implementation, namely:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Write booleans as &apos;1&apos;/&apos;0&apos; instead of &quot;true&quot;/&quot;false&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Parse empty lists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The code appears identical in the current master branch. I&apos;ve attached a patch with the changes I&apos;ve made, but they&apos;ve only been tested for my use case; I haven&apos;t looked at any specs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
